bug.short_desc: Opening and closing nautilus during a file transfer results in a gui bug.
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1173294 Screenshot of the gui problem
Description of problem: When i close and open nautilus again during a file transfer, the transfer popup automatically opens in a weird location with a black/grey bar above it. (see attached screenshot) The activities tab seems to count this popup as a seperate window because it has it's own window in the activities tab.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 3.20.1
How reproducible: Every time
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Start a file transfer (in my case from a nas) 2. Close nautilus (file transfer runs in the background now) 3. Open nautilus
Actual results: Nautilus opens and i see the file transfer window popup in a weird location. (see attached screenshot)
Expected results: I don't expect the file transfer window to open when i reopen nautilus and certainly not in a weird location with a bar above it.
Additional info: This is a fresh install of fedora 24 on a toshiba c55 sattelite
My fedora install is fully up to date (sudo dnf update).

https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=766526
This bug has been fixed upstream, but I don't know if it's released yet.
When can we see nautilus updated to the newer version?
